# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Find the maximum length path for every children of each node and update ```res``` accordingly.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
**Step 1: -** Standing on a node, we will ask ```helper``` function to bring us the length of the maximum path for each children.
**Step 2: -** Store the atmost 2 maximum values obtained in min heap ```pq```.
**Step 3: -** Store the 2 elements of min heap ```pq``` in ```len1``` and ```len2```.
**Step 4: -** Update ```res``` as 
1. By considering maximum of two longest paths obtained i.e. ```res = max (res, 1+max (len1, len2))```.
2. By considering sum of two longest paths obtained i.e. ```res = max (res, 1+len1+len2)```.

**Step 5: -** Return ```0``` if ```prev == s[node]-'a'``` is ```true``` else return ```1 + max(len1, len2)```(*since responsibility of ```helper``` is to provide the longest path containing current node*).
# Complexity
- Time complexity: ```O(N*log 2)```
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: ```O(height of the tree + 2*n(adjacency list))```
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int helper (vector<int>* adj, string &s, int vertex, int&res, int prev, int parent){
// Base case
        if ((adj[vertex].size () == 1 && adj[vertex][0] == parent) || adj[0].size () == 0){
            res = max (res, 1);

            return (prev != -1 && prev == s[vertex]-'a') ? 0 : 1;
        }


        priority_queue<int, vector<int>, greater<int>> pq;

        for (auto x: adj[vertex]){
            if (x != parent){
                int ans = helper (adj, s, x, res, s[vertex]-'a', vertex);

                if (pq.size () < 2) pq.push (ans);
                else{
                    if (pq.top () < ans){
                        pq.pop ();

                        pq.push (ans);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        auto len1 = pq.top ();
        pq.pop ();

        int len2 = 0;
        if (pq.empty () == 0) {
            len2 = pq.top ();
            pq.pop ();
        }

        res = max (res, 1+max (len1, len2));
        res = max (res, 1+len1+len2);

        return (prev != -1 && prev == s[vertex]-'a') ? 0 : 1 + max (len1,len2);
    }
    int longestPath(vector<int>& parent, string s) {
        int n = parent.size ();
        vector<int> adj[n];

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++){
            adj[i].push_back (parent[i]);
            adj[parent[i]].push_back (i);
        }

        int res = 0;
        helper (adj, s, 0, res, -1, -1);

        return res;
    }
};
```

