# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
at each node, the longest path is formed by traversing from the deppest valid traversal (from that node) to the node and then to the second deepest valid traversal.

A little optimization would be needed, if we start a new traversal at each node, the time complexity will be $$O(n^2)$$. So Here, we try to do that in a single DFT.

![A.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/03bd2cf4-4e45-472e-bcdd-6f5788cd7082_1673595940.1588051.png)


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Make the Adjacency List (here, I have changed the structure to an out tree rooted at $$0$$)
2. Perform DFT. The function `longetsPathAt(int n, List<List<Integer>> adj, String s)`
    - returns the deepest path from node n, such that the path has no 2 adjacent nodes assigned the same character. 
    - Updates the global variable `res` as `res = Math.max(res, max1 + max2 - 1)`
    - Trverses nodes that violates the forth-mentioned conditions separately, for the longest path may go through them alike.
3. return `res`
# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    int res = 0;
    int longetsPathAt(int n, List<List<Integer>> adj, String s)
    {
        int max1 = 1, max2 = 1;
        for(int child : adj.get(n))
        {
            if(s.charAt(child) != s.charAt(n))
            {
                int path = longetsPathAt(child, adj, s) + 1;
                if(path > max1)
                {
                    max2 = max1;
                    max1 = path;
                }
                else if(path > max2) max2 = path;
            }
            else longetsPathAt(child, adj, s);
        }
        res = Math.max(res, max1 + max2 - 1);
        return max1;
    }
    public int longestPath(int[] parent, String s) {
        List<List<Integer>> adj = new ArrayList<>();
        for(int i = 0 ; i < parent.length; i++) adj.add(new ArrayList<>());
        for(int i = 0 ; i < parent.length; i++) if(parent[i] != -1) adj.get(parent[i]).add(i);
        longetsPathAt(0, adj, s);
        return res;        
    }
}
```

