solutions.content:
# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
DFS will be required to get the Max path but we need to figure out a way to check which path is the longest.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The longest path can be 1 of two types as can be seen in the provided examples:
1. A node along with path along one of its subtrees

![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/a927aa6e-1a9b-4264-a835-a4f0bff0b73f_1673591686.1253104.png)

2. A node and path along two of its subtrees

![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/4148bf9c-2f9e-4e33-ab37-2b408fd49c58_1673591840.1773436.png)

So during DFS we can only consider path along two subtrees at max for a certain node. And the path that can be returned to the parent of a node should be the maxpath along one of the subtrees of the node.
To achieve this we will maintain two path lengths maximum path & second maximum path for each call to the recursive dfs function. And the path lengths from subtrees will only be considered if the subtree root does not have the same label as parent.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxval;
    int dfs(vector<vector<int>>& tree, int node, string& s, int p) {
        int smaxpath = 0, maxpath = 0;
        for(int val : tree[node]) {
            //to avoid call to parent
            if(val != p) {
                //dfs call to a child node
                int clen = dfs(tree, val, s, node);
                //checking if parent - child labels are different
                if(s[node] != s[val]) {
                    //updating maximum path & second maximum path
                    if(clen > maxpath) {
                        smaxpath = maxpath;
                        maxpath = clen;
                    } else if(clen > smaxpath) {
                        smaxpath = clen;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        //to consider the current node
        maxpath += 1;
        //updating the maximum path length so far
        maxval = max(maxval, maxpath + smaxpath);
        //returning only the maximum path from subtrees
        return maxpath;
    }

    int longestPath(vector<int>& parent, string s) {
        vector<vector<int>> tree(parent.size());
        //adjacency list for tree
        for(int i = 1; i < parent.size(); i++) {
            tree[i].push_back(parent[i]);
            tree[parent[i]].push_back(i);
        }
        maxval = 0;
        dfs(tree, 0, s, -1);
        return maxval;
    }
};
```

