# Approach
1. Form the Adjacency List of the Tree.
2. Perform DFS on each subtree and calculate the Longest One way<Only travelling downward in direction of the leaves> path.
3. Then calculate the longest path of that subtree by adding the longest 2 paths +1 because of the root node and update the res value
4. then return the longest one way path +1.

**NOTE --> Remenber to check that the root node of the subtree and the child node does not have same label!!**

