# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
My intuition for this problem is to solve using example of tree with largest diameter, but the only catch here is we can add height of tree of one side if corresponding character between child and parent are different,

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
we will call dfs for left sub tree and right sub tree.
if its current character is different to both left and right child 
then we can assume left tree's height + right tree's height + 1(parent itself) will contribute in maximising length.
for this we will select two max length of child's thats why i used priority queue.
but we return max length to parent on each step.

# Complexity
