# Intuition
Based On Depth First Search(DFS)

# Approach
First we will create a adjacency list considering the edges to be directed from parent to child.Now we will apply DFS to it. For longest chain for every node, we will consider two longest straight chain from its children which are not having same character as of node(as tree is n-ary).Now answer will be max of answer and the sum of two longest chains of children +1(node itself). And from here we will return longest straight chain to its parent.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(n) for creating adjacency list.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int ans=0;
    int dfs(int curr,int n,vector<vector<int> > &adj,string &s){
        int temp=0;
        int most=0,more=0;
        for(int i=0;i<adj[curr].size();i++){
            int left=dfs(adj[curr][i],n,adj,s);
            if(s[curr]!=s[adj[curr][i]]){
                if(left>most) more=most,most=left;
                else if(left>more) more=left;
            }
        }
        ans=max(ans,1+more+most);
        return most+1;
    }
    int longestPath(vector<int>& parent, string s) {
        int n=parent.size();
        // creating adjacency list
        vector<vector<int> > adj(n);
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            adj[parent[i]].push_back(i);
        }
        dfs(0,n,adj,s);
        return ans;
    }
};
```

